Hehe Ok, I'll lay off the DAoC; that's just what popped to mind when I heard them talking about endurance.  :-)  That game had its own problems, anyway - I left it, too.

To be honest, I started the monk when I retured from my FIRST retirement, mainly because I had retired shortly after Kunark came out and sold my enchanter that fall.  Whoops.  At least the buyer was an acquaintance of mine.  Anyway, I truly enjoyed the class, and I was damned good at it, but shortly after SoV came out, I tried EQ again as an enchanter on a friend's account, got up to the mid-30's in a few weeks (hey, I was rusty!), and discovered the magic resist hell that is/was Velious.  So when I got my own new account, I decided to try the only other class that interested me, the monk.

It was fun, both the insane melee and the pulling.  (You'll always endear yourself to a monk with comments like 'I've never SEEN so much damange spam go by so fast'.)  I've good memories of both, honestly, although, as you said, some of the later pulling could get a bit painful.

My problem is the tedium - I grew amazingly tired of spending 6+ hours LFG as a monk, being told they'd rather have a 50 rogue or beastlord.  I wanted to fight; I wanted to perma-pull (even if some whiners complained I spent more time out bringing mobs to the group than standing there fighting in PoN).  I didn't want to sit on my tail all night long shouting for a group and hoping some desperate group took pity.  Add in the AC nerf from last year, and I had suddenly lost even most of my ability to solo, as my gear was a bit sub-standard, since I preferred to let people who needed the drops get them rather than getting them myself and selling them.  I don't mind soloing on occasion, but after 3 weeks of alternating soloing (slowly, as even LDC's did a lot of damage to scaled arse now) and fruitless evenings LFG, I got fed up and left.

(And I don't join guilds to get stuff; I join guids with people I want to be around, and mine had fallen apart previously.)

If I come back, all of the above will almost definitely lead me to going back to enchanting, even though the thought of practicing JC back up is...painful.  All because the changes sucked away any of the joy that was Hizuka.  He'll still be there for emergencies, but unless things have drastically changed, and by the talks about melee balancing, they haven't, then I'll probaby be going enchanter again.  We play to enjoy ourselves, after all.

